#: of numpy.nanpercentile:34
msgid ""
"This parameter specifies the method to use for estimating the percentile.  "
"There are many different methods, some unique to NumPy. See the notes for "
"explanation.  The options sorted by their R type as summarized in the H&F "
"paper [Re21b1d0b0470-1]_ are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:39
msgid "'inverted_cdf'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:40
msgid "'averaged_inverted_cdf'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:41
msgid "'closest_observation'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:42
msgid "'interpolated_inverted_cdf'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:43
msgid "'hazen'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:44
msgid "'weibull'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:45
msgid "'linear'  (default)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:46
msgid "'median_unbiased'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:47
msgid "'normal_unbiased'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:49
msgid ""
"The first three methods are discontinuous.  NumPy further defines the "
"following discontinuous variations of the default 'linear' (7.) option:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:52
msgid "'lower'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:53
msgid "'higher',"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:54
msgid "'midpoint'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:55
msgid "'nearest'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:57
msgid ""
"This argument was previously called \"interpolation\" and only offered the "
"\"linear\" default and last four options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:70
msgid "**keepdims**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:62
msgid ""
"If this is set to True, the axes which are reduced are left in the result as "
"dimensions with size one. With this option, the result will broadcast "
"correctly against the original array `a`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:66
msgid ""
"If this is anything but the default value it will be passed through (in the "
"special case of an empty array) to the `mean` function of the underlying "
"array.  If the array is a sub-class and `mean` does not have the kwarg "
"`keepdims` this will raise a RuntimeError."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:83
msgid "**weights**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:-1
msgid "array_like, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:73
msgid ""
"An array of weights associated with the values in `a`. Each value in `a` "
"contributes to the percentile according to its associated weight. The "
"weights array can either be 1-D (in which case its length must be the size "
"of `a` along the given axis) or of the same shape as `a`. If `weights=None`, "
"then all data in `a` are assumed to have a weight equal to one. Only "
"`method=\"inverted_cdf\"` supports weights."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:0
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:101
msgid "**percentile**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:-1
msgid "scalar or ndarray"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.nanpercentile:88
msgid ""
"If `q` is a single percentile and `axis=None`, then the result is a scalar. "
"If multiple percentiles are given, first axis of the result corresponds to "
"the percentiles. The other axes are the axes that remain after the reduction "
"of `a`. If the input contains integers or floats smaller than ``float64``, "
"the output data-type is ``float64``. Otherwise, the output data-type is the "
"same as that of the input. If `out` is specified, that array is returned "
"instead."
msgstr ""

